 Check for JAVA is there or not.[On command promt- java -version]

2. If it is there then proceed to next step otherwise install jdk and set path on Windows environment variable.

3. Download Apache Maven [Visit Maven official website]

4. Add both M2_HOME and MAVEN_HOME variables in the Windows environment, and point it to your Maven folder.

5. Add To PATH - Update PATH variable, append Maven bin folder – %M2_HOME%\bin, so that you can run the Maven’s command everywhere.

5. Verification - Done, to verify it, run mvn –version in the command prompt.

